<s> [INST] You are an expert in Natural Language Inference (NLI). Please list all possible explanations why the the following statement is true (entailment) given the context below without introductory phrases. 
Context: My unborn children will never appear on the Today show. 
Statement: No direct descendent of mine will ever be a guest of the Today show. 
Answer: [/INST] 1. The speaker is referring to their unborn children as their direct descendants.
2. The Today show includes guests who are not biologically related to the host or interviewer.
3. The speaker's unborn children will never become famous or newsworthy.
4. The speaker does not plan on having any more children after their unborn children.
5. The Today show will not be airing new episodes in the future.
6. The speaker's unborn children will not be alive in the future.
7. The Today show will cease to exist before the speaker's unborn children are born.
8. The speaker's unborn children will never be invited as guests on the Today show.
9. The speaker is certain that their unborn children will not appear on the Today show.
10. The speaker has the ability to prevent their direct descendants from appearing on the Today show.</s>